
UPDATE designers SET
  biography = 'Bruno Moinard Éditions was established in 2014 by interior architect Bruno Moinard — founder of the Moinard-Bétaille agency at 41 avenue Montaigne, Paris — as a dedicated furniture, lighting, rugs, and objects line. The collection distils over four decades of architectural practice into refined, collectible pieces, each produced entirely in France with master artisans.

Moinard''s architectural career began at Ecart International alongside Andrée Putman, where he spent fifteen years shaping the interiors of the 1980s — from the Morgans Hotel in New York and boutiques for Karl Lagerfeld and Thierry Mugler to the interior of five Concordes for Air France. After founding his own practice in 1995, he became the architect of the global Cartier boutique network — a partnership spanning over 470 stores across six continents. His hospitality portfolio includes the Plaza Athénée Hotel in Paris, the Four Seasons at Ten Trinity Square in London, the Hôtel Capella at Galaxy Macau, and the Diaoyutai-MGM hotels in Chengdu, alongside extensive residential commissions worldwide.

The Éditions line translates this depth of spatial understanding into objects: tables, consoles, lamps, mirrors, and decorative accessories whose proportions, materials, and details bear the signature economy of line that defines Moinard''s architecture. Collections are presented at the Rue Jacob flagship in Paris and carried in eleven cities including New York, Shanghai, London, Miami, and Vancouver. In a return to his roots, Moinard has also developed several furniture models for Ecart International, the house where his career began.',
  specialty = 'Furniture · Lighting · Objects · Interior architecture',
  notable_works = 'Bruno Moinard Éditions furniture and lighting line (est. 2014). Rue Jacob flagship, Paris. Collections carried in 11 cities worldwide. Furniture designs for Ecart International. Founded by Bruno Moinard of Moinard-Bétaille (Cartier global architect, Plaza Athénée, Four Seasons London).',
  philosophy = 'A designer — passionately, temperamentally and instinctively — I am proud to produce 100% French work and to contribute to the sustainability of this industry.
— Bruno Moinard'
WHERE id = '81a2a7fd-ec96-45b8-9043-8862a7cf2922';
